The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Syed Ali Mondal, 47, allegedly throttled and killed his seven-year-old son Munna on Sunday morning to take out his anger against his wife, who he suspected of having an extra-marital affair. The incident occurred in Khardah, on the northern fringes of the city. Praveen Kumar, superintendent of North 24-Parganas police, said Syed was Munna?s stepfather. He suspects his third wife Jahanara of having an affair with a youth. Ali, who runs a grocery shop, returned home late on Saturday and did not find his wife. Munna told him that his mother had gone out to visit a neighbour. Infuriated, Syed immediately pounced on Munna. He has been arrested. 

 A fire broke out on the sixth floor of the Green Building, on the Calcutta Medical College and Hospital compound, on Sunday night. Two tenders doused the blaze in 15 minutes. There was no casualty or loss of property. According to fire brigade and Medical College officials, the fire broke out in an abandoned staircase, where old and unused clothes, bandages and other material were dumped. 

 Amar Dutta, 35, a trader, was shot dead by two unidentified men while he was returning home in Baruipur, on the southern fringes of the city, on Sunday evening.

 To strengthen its distribution system, CESC will carry out repairs on the 33 KV overhead lines between the Fort Gloster and the Ludlow distribution stations on January 9 and 16. Supply to consumers in Phuleswar, Sejberia, Ludlow, Jagannathpur and Chengail may be affected between 10.30 am and 4.30 pm on the two days.

 Sleuths from the detective department arrested three alleged criminals, including Kana Mastan, from a hideout in Jadavpur on Sunday in connection with the murder of Gouri Shankar Chatterjee. Chatterjee, in his late 70s, was shot dead by a gang on December 17 on Khagen Chatterjee Road, in Dum Dum. 

 Nine shops were destroyed after a fire broke out at the old bus stand in Uluberia, Howrah, early on Sunday morning. Two tenders doused the blaze. Residents held a demonstration, demanding a fire station in the locality. 

 Around 30 shanties on Geelani Khan Road, under Tiljala police station, were destroyed in a fire that broke out around 3.15 pm on Sunday. Six tenders battled for hours to bring the blaze under control. 

 Some unidentified criminals partly tonsured a woman in Sonarpur, on the southern fringes of the city, over a property dispute on Saturday night. The 32-year-old woman has lodged a police complaint. The woman?s husband alleged that the goons were hired by his relatives.

